{
  "texts": [
    "They can be sensitive to noisy data, outliers, and variations in input, which can lead to suboptimal representations and reconstructions (Singh and Ogunfunmi 2022).",
    "AEs can be prone to overfitting, especially when trained on limited data.",
    "Additionally, they may not inherently preserve the spatial or temporal locality of data during training.",
    "This can be problematic for tasks where preserving the local structure is essential, such as image segmentation or sequence modeling (Liu et al. 2023).",
    "Furthermore, AEs tend to capture lower-order features and may struggle to represent complex, higher-order relationships in the data."
  ]
}